1
00:00:04,159 --> 00:00:06,960
We will continue with
the apprentice class on weekends.

2
00:00:09,199 --> 00:00:12,116
Am I going to do acupuncture
or prepare herbal medicine?

3
00:00:12,199 --> 00:00:13,373
You are sweeping the floor.

4
00:00:16,880 --> 00:00:18,080
During this period,

5
00:00:18,359 --> 00:00:21,119
we will invite influential teachers

6
00:00:21,436 --> 00:00:24,637
from different schools

7
00:00:24,720 --> 00:00:26,676
and with different specialities

8
00:00:26,759 --> 00:00:27,916
to give you lectures.

9
00:00:27,999 --> 00:00:29,916
We hope that everyone of you

10
00:00:29,999 --> 00:00:32,157
can find out a field that you like

11
00:00:32,240 --> 00:00:34,197
and is most suitable for you

12
00:00:34,280 --> 00:00:36,799
during this learning period.

13
00:00:38,867 --> 00:00:39,890
You don't have a choice.

14
00:00:39,973 --> 00:00:41,292
You'll just have to follow me.

15
00:00:41,880 --> 00:00:43,917
Mr Ren, my paid leave is over.

16
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:45,477
I have to return to the hospital to work.

17
00:00:45,560 --> 00:00:47,876
I will frequently take leave
from the apprentice class.

18
00:00:47,959 --> 00:00:48,957
It's not a problem.

19
00:00:49,040 --> 00:00:52,120
You and Xing Xing
are both healthcare workers.

20
00:00:52,280 --> 00:00:55,596
The reason why I am teaching you
is because I hope that

21
00:00:55,679 --> 00:00:57,288
you can apply TCM to your daily life.

22
00:00:57,920 --> 00:00:59,200
Go on. Go back to work.

23
00:01:00,240 --> 00:01:01,437
Shi Yan, for the classes you miss,

24
00:01:01,520 --> 00:01:04,117
you can ask your classmates later
and make up for them.

25
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:05,200
Got it.

26
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:07,200
Tou,

27
00:01:07,360 --> 00:01:08,877
you need surplus grain
to distribute porridge.

28
00:01:08,960 --> 00:01:11,917
As for this saline-alkali land of
yours, you can keep it to yourself.

29
00:01:12,959 --> 00:01:16,200
I'd better seek help from
our top-performing student, Ms Yang.

30
00:01:16,520 --> 00:01:18,397
I'll trouble you with this in the future.

31
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:19,480
Thank you in advance.

32
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:21,720
I have run out of surplus grain.

33
00:01:23,113 --> 00:01:25,027
You are a rich mine,
overflowing with wealth.

34
00:01:25,335 --> 00:01:26,335
Professor Ren.

35
00:01:28,480 --> 00:01:29,476
Are they the mother and daughter
you told me about?

36
00:01:29,559 --> 00:01:30,559
Yes, yes.

37
00:01:30,760 --> 00:01:32,320
Zhu Xia and Ding Jian Xi.

38
00:01:33,440 --> 00:01:35,196
-Hi.
-Professor Ren.

39
00:01:35,279 --> 00:01:36,845
Finally, we've been waiting for you.

40
00:01:37,019 --> 00:01:38,979
Please help my daughter.

41
00:01:39,279 --> 00:01:41,319
If even you tell us that it's hopeless,

42
00:01:41,760 --> 00:01:43,760
then she can only stay
this way until she dies.

43
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:46,599
Don't talk about death all the time.

44
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:47,840
In this place,

45
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:49,997
it's not easy to die even if you want to.

46
00:01:50,080 --> 00:01:51,570
I've been briefed

47
00:01:51,680 --> 00:01:53,399
about her condition.

48
00:01:53,687 --> 00:01:54,887
Let me take a look.

49
00:01:55,040 --> 00:01:56,640
Come. Easy, easy.

50
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:27,280
Do you feel anything?

51
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:31,560
Her condition

52
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:32,957
is basically incurable.

53
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:36,258
Western doctors said that she would
stay this way for the rest of her life.

54
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:38,256
Professor Ren, if even you say

55
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:39,360
there is no way,

56
00:02:39,453 --> 00:02:40,453
then...

57
00:02:51,153 --> 00:02:52,153
Don't worry.

58
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:54,560
There is a way.

59
00:02:56,947 --> 00:02:57,947
There is a way.

60
00:02:58,240 --> 00:02:59,679
I just remembered that

61
00:02:59,799 --> 00:03:02,200
there was this master
I apprenticed under before.

62
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:03,223
He taught me about

63
00:03:03,306 --> 00:03:04,716
bone resetting

64
00:03:04,799 --> 00:03:07,400
and spinal rehabilitation.

65
00:03:08,040 --> 00:03:10,040
I recall writing it down in a notebook.

66
00:03:12,920 --> 00:03:16,356
Oh, right. There is a notebook
in my desk drawer.

67
00:03:16,440 --> 00:03:17,440
Please get it for me.

68
00:03:18,640 --> 00:03:20,597
That means my daughter's
condition is curable?

69
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:23,200
This medicine

70
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:25,760
might be difficult to find.

71
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:27,504
It's okay. Just tell me.

72
00:03:27,587 --> 00:03:28,437
I'll do everything

73
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:29,559
I can to find it.

74
00:03:30,640 --> 00:03:31,640
Is it the one?

75
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:34,840
Let me see.

76
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:39,000
No peeking.

77
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:42,037
If you look without my permission,
you will get red eyes.

78
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:43,120
Go over there.

79
00:03:52,986 --> 00:03:53,986
This should be the one.

80
00:03:55,640 --> 00:03:58,317
Tiles from the top of kitchen stove,

81
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:00,920
from an old house
that is over 300 years old,

82
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:02,360
soak it in child's urine

83
00:04:03,519 --> 00:04:05,560
for 21 days.

84
00:04:06,139 --> 00:04:08,499
Grind it into powder and
take it with the rice wine.

85
00:04:09,918 --> 00:04:11,319
Take... Take it?

86
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:14,480
You mean, drink it?

87
00:04:15,166 --> 00:04:17,006
Pee and tiles?

88
00:04:18,020 --> 00:04:19,020
Amazing.

89
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:20,717
TCM practitioners aren't afraid to bluff.

90
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,931
-I'll go and find it now.
-Mind your own business.

91
00:04:24,713 --> 00:04:25,913
This should be the remedy.

92
00:04:26,399 --> 00:04:27,399
But you know,

93
00:04:28,520 --> 00:04:31,879
it's not easy to find houses that are

94
00:04:32,393 --> 00:04:33,611
over 300 years old nowadays.

95
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:35,957
There are so many places in the country.

96
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,397
I just need to find one.

97
00:04:37,480 --> 00:04:38,374
I would find them

98
00:04:38,457 --> 00:04:40,457
even if I had to remove
the beams of the house.

99
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:42,279
You can't do that.

100
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:44,957
That's illegal.

101
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:47,080
You will get arrested.

102
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:49,811
-You know, I was arrested last time...
-Tou Tou...

103
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:04,571
Don't you have an appetite?
Why aren't you eating?

104
00:05:05,520 --> 00:05:06,955
Quan, is something bothering you?

105
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:13,880
Why are you sighing?

106
00:05:14,279 --> 00:05:16,159
The dishes today aren't very appetizing.

107
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:19,143
What you make for us is better than this.

108
00:05:20,092 --> 00:05:21,092
But it's healthy.

109
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:24,520
How about you ask Roubecca
to give you some of her salad?

110
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:25,680
Would you like some?

111
00:05:25,960 --> 00:05:28,160
I was thinking about Ding Jian Xi
and her mother.

112
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:31,680
You also think that Mr Ren's remedy
is too far-fetched?

113
00:05:32,785 --> 00:05:34,706
I just feel bad for her parents.

114
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:38,557
She and her mum have to go through this.

115
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:40,119
If this happened on me,

116
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:43,399
my parents would probably faint on
the spot upon hearing the news.

117
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:47,680
Yes. It's true that
it's quite miserable.

118
00:05:48,559 --> 00:05:49,437
Tian Zhen,

119
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:50,437
they are already so miserable.

120
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:52,564
How could your dad
still blatantly deceive them?

121
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:53,717
Listen to this.

122
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:55,758
He can cure a patient
with a completely broken spine

123
00:05:55,841 --> 00:05:58,480
by using 300-year-old tiles
and child's urine?

124
00:05:59,279 --> 00:06:00,319
This is not medicine,

125
00:06:00,520 --> 00:06:01,680
it's witchcraft.

126
00:06:03,080 --> 00:06:05,437
Never mind whether
it's medicine or witchcraft.

127
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:07,129
If it works, that's all that matters.

128
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:08,356
In traditional Chinese characters,
the character for

129
00:06:08,439 --> 00:06:10,803
"medicine" originally had
the character for "shaman" below it.

130
00:06:10,886 --> 00:06:11,757
Tian Zhen,

131
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:13,120
this is unlike you.

132
00:06:13,960 --> 00:06:16,157
You have received
basic education in materialism.

133
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:17,277
What is the science in this?

134
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:18,480
Do you really believe

135
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:21,800
that paralysis can be cured with
300-year-old tiles and child's urine?

136
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:23,160
Yes, I believe it.

137
00:06:23,839 --> 00:06:26,879
Otherwise, why do we have so few houses
that are over 300 years old

138
00:06:26,993 --> 00:06:27,993
compared to Europe?

139
00:06:29,427 --> 00:06:31,036
Do you TCM practitioners
all think like this?

140
00:06:31,119 --> 00:06:33,163
In Li Shi Zhen's
"Compendium of Materia Medica",

141
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:34,317
he wrote that shoe sole mud,

142
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:35,240
manure pit mud,

143
00:06:35,323 --> 00:06:36,677
and foot-wrapping cloth
are all medicinal.

144
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:37,953
But look at the Westerners,

145
00:06:38,332 --> 00:06:39,920
they have Moscow Mathematical Papyrus,

146
00:06:40,003 --> 00:06:41,381
Rhind Mathematical Papyrus,

147
00:06:41,464 --> 00:06:42,437
and later works like Euclid's Elements

148
00:06:42,520 --> 00:06:43,726
and The Art of Calculation.

149
00:06:44,399 --> 00:06:45,636
I understand that acupuncture

150
00:06:45,719 --> 00:06:47,360
might work for spinal cord injuries,

151
00:06:47,608 --> 00:06:48,899
but this particular remedy

152
00:06:49,288 --> 00:06:50,489
sounds toxic.

153
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:52,196
How could it possibly be effective?

154
00:06:52,279 --> 00:06:54,597
This is the difference
between folk remedies

155
00:06:54,680 --> 00:06:56,999
and actual science.

156
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:00,717
What does that mean?

157
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:02,999
Didn't Xin Zheng say it's curable?

158
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:05,447
How's acupuncture different from
taking medicine?

159
00:07:07,960 --> 00:07:09,600
Tou, the spine

160
00:07:10,399 --> 00:07:11,680
is like this bone.

161
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:13,677
The vertebrae

162
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:15,437
are connected by ligaments,
muscles, and nerves.

163
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:17,680
This way, the central nervous system
in your brain

164
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:20,601
can transmit signals to
every part of your body,

165
00:07:20,684 --> 00:07:21,717
allowing you to run,

166
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:22,677
jump,

167
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:24,847
and feel sensations such as
cold, heat, and pain.

168
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:27,360
But Jian Xi,

169
00:07:28,399 --> 00:07:29,559
from her waist here,

170
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:32,720
it's broken.

171
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:34,476
The bone is broken but the flesh
surrounding it remains intact.

172
00:07:34,559 --> 00:07:36,920
Modern medicine is capable
of rejoining broken bones,

173
00:07:37,160 --> 00:07:38,144
nerves,

174
00:07:38,227 --> 00:07:40,106
and even muscles.

175
00:07:40,453 --> 00:07:43,012
However, once the signal transmission
is interrupted,

176
00:07:43,159 --> 00:07:44,637
reconnecting it

177
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:45,920
is highly complex.

178
00:07:46,119 --> 00:07:48,380
Modern medicine has not yet
found a solution to this.

179
00:07:50,320 --> 00:07:51,255
I may not

180
00:07:51,338 --> 00:07:52,778
fully understand neurology,

181
00:07:52,967 --> 00:07:54,007
but I think

182
00:07:54,366 --> 00:07:55,717
the regeneration of neurons

183
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:58,401
can be facilitated through methods
such as acupuncture and moxibustion,

184
00:07:58,484 --> 00:08:00,123
which involve repetitive stimulation.

185
00:08:00,399 --> 00:08:02,090
Such methods are likely to be effective.

186
00:08:02,173 --> 00:08:03,173
However, the idea

187
00:08:03,960 --> 00:08:05,520
of simply consuming medication

188
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:07,036
can restore sensation

189
00:08:07,119 --> 00:08:08,036
to a paralysed person

190
00:08:08,119 --> 00:08:09,960
does not seem logically sound

191
00:08:10,399 --> 00:08:11,237
to me.

192
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:12,320
Rebecca,

193
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:14,040
great minds think alike.

194
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:15,320
Give me five.

195
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:18,240
Tian Zhen,

196
00:08:19,559 --> 00:08:21,640
how confident do you think
Mr Ren is this time?

197
00:08:22,287 --> 00:08:23,607
I can't figure him out.

198
00:08:26,646 --> 00:08:27,646
My dad said

199
00:08:27,960 --> 00:08:29,597
that our ancestors
believed it to be effective.

200
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:30,680
Thank you.

201
00:08:43,533 --> 00:08:44,533
I think...

202
00:08:46,763 --> 00:08:48,279
I think you are cool.

203
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:52,560
You look cool when you work.

204
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:57,277
I think you look so cool in everything

205
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:58,477
you do.

206
00:08:58,560 --> 00:09:00,639
Don't you find it strange?
You are so handsome.

207
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:03,745
What you said is already
considered sexual harassment.

208
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:08,197
Seriously? This is sexual harassment
just because I complimented you?

209
00:09:08,719 --> 00:09:10,240
I can't even compliment you now?

210
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:13,839
Now this is sexual harassment!

211
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:15,360
You...

212
00:09:30,159 --> 00:09:31,599
I'm sorry.

213
00:09:32,599 --> 00:09:33,599
It's broken.

214
00:09:33,719 --> 00:09:35,079
I stepped on it.

215
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:37,360
(Xu Jie)
I'm really sorry.

216
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:39,957
All right. No need for any explanations.

217
00:09:40,040 --> 00:09:41,360
How do you want to solve this?

218
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:48,560
I will

219
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:51,159
compensate you.

220
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:54,000
I will pay you the money
you paid for this.

221
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:56,240
Over 10,000 yuan.

222
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:00,959
Over 10,000 yuan?

223
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:04,120
Hang on...

224
00:10:04,240 --> 00:10:05,399
She will pay you back.

225
00:10:05,719 --> 00:10:06,717
Don't worry, sir.

226
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:08,597
She will definitely pay you back for
these glasses at the original price.

227
00:10:08,680 --> 00:10:10,507
It'll just cost her
three months' salaries.

228
00:10:16,280 --> 00:10:17,520
Here's the thing, sir.

229
00:10:18,187 --> 00:10:19,492
Let me explain the logic here.

230
00:10:20,307 --> 00:10:22,184
All I did was complimenting him just now.

231
00:10:22,267 --> 00:10:23,744
Is there anything wrong
with saying he looks cool?

232
00:10:23,827 --> 00:10:24,744
No, right?

233
00:10:24,827 --> 00:10:26,436
And he just turned around and hit me.

234
00:10:26,747 --> 00:10:28,547
I bumped into you because he hit me.

235
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:30,224
I wouldn't have done so
if he hadn't hit me.

236
00:10:30,307 --> 00:10:32,583
I wouldn't have stepped on your glasses
if he hadn't hit me.

237
00:10:32,666 --> 00:10:34,984
I wouldn't have had to pay you
back 10,000 yuan if he hadn't hit me.

238
00:10:35,067 --> 00:10:36,904
Am I right?
So, he's responsible for this.

239
00:10:36,987 --> 00:10:38,093
Ask him to pay you back.

240
00:10:38,507 --> 00:10:39,463
He's rich.

241
00:10:39,546 --> 00:10:41,747
This big medical centre
belongs to his family.

242
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:42,957
He's a son from a rich family.

243
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:44,117
He's got lots of money,

244
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:45,200
you know?

245
00:10:45,546 --> 00:10:46,590
What are you looking at?

246
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:48,599
That's right.
I'm moral blackmailing you.

247
00:10:49,546 --> 00:10:51,146
You are Professor Ren's son?

248
00:10:53,267 --> 00:10:54,507
I am. And you are?

249
00:10:56,307 --> 00:10:57,906
You saved my daughter.

250
00:10:58,307 --> 00:10:59,427
I'm Xu Meng's father.

251
00:11:02,747 --> 00:11:03,791
Do you remember Xu Meng?

252
00:11:03,920 --> 00:11:04,920
How is she doing now?

253
00:11:06,187 --> 00:11:07,187
Not really good.

254
00:11:08,307 --> 00:11:10,568
Do you still want us
to pay you back for the glasses?

255
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:14,689
She lost her sanity?

256
00:11:14,772 --> 00:11:15,772
She lost her sanity?

257
00:11:18,987 --> 00:11:21,784
Meng Meng has always been
well behaved since she was young.

258
00:11:21,867 --> 00:11:22,987
As her parents,

259
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:25,023
we haven't had to worry much
about her life and studies.

260
00:11:25,106 --> 00:11:28,987
Perhaps we've been too overprotective
of her since she was little.

261
00:11:29,103 --> 00:11:31,026
She just can't tell right from wrong,

262
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:33,400
so she was tricked by a boy.

263
00:11:33,483 --> 00:11:35,227
Do you know this boy?

264
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:37,080
No. She wouldn't tell us.

265
00:11:37,212 --> 00:11:39,343
Her mother and I have been too busy
with our work.

266
00:11:41,187 --> 00:11:42,187
Actually,

267
00:11:42,747 --> 00:11:43,904
we only learned about this

268
00:11:43,987 --> 00:11:45,292
a little earlier than you did.

269
00:11:45,507 --> 00:11:47,029
I'm sure you didn't ask her before.

270
00:11:47,187 --> 00:11:50,101
Maybe she had mentioned it,
and you just didn't pay attention to it.

271
00:11:53,187 --> 00:11:54,187
