821
00:34:20,186 --> 00:34:21,197
the boys in the supermarket last time.

822
00:34:21,280 --> 00:34:22,984
Remember her?
You've met before, Meng Meng.

823
00:34:23,067 --> 00:34:23,984
It's me.

824
00:34:24,067 --> 00:34:25,067
She's Sun Tou Tou.

825
00:34:27,666 --> 00:34:28,666
Hang on.

826
00:34:29,307 --> 00:34:30,237
Meng Meng,

827
00:34:30,320 --> 00:34:31,424
don't worry.

828
00:34:31,507 --> 00:34:33,383
Don't mind these annoying boys.

829
00:34:33,466 --> 00:34:34,823
If you need anything,

830
00:34:34,906 --> 00:34:35,906
just come to me.

831
00:34:36,320 --> 00:34:38,863
We are roommates starting today.
We're going to live together!

832
00:34:38,946 --> 00:34:40,704
What are you talking about, Sun Tou Tou?

833
00:34:40,787 --> 00:34:41,823
She's scared!

834
00:34:41,906 --> 00:34:42,783
-Knock it off.
-Scared of what?

835
00:34:42,866 --> 00:34:43,664
-Give me a hug!
-Leave her alone.

836
00:34:43,747 --> 00:34:44,747
I'm your roommate.

837
00:34:54,760 --> 00:34:56,520
It is the middle of March.

838
00:34:56,799 --> 00:34:58,880
The garden is green with flowers.

839
00:34:59,107 --> 00:35:00,934
The morning doves
are singing in the house,

840
00:35:01,107 --> 00:35:02,946
indulging in spring sleep by the window.

841
00:35:03,520 --> 00:35:06,520
The cooing dove flaps its wings,
indicating the arrival of Grain Rain.

842
00:35:09,226 --> 00:35:10,226
Nephew.

843
00:35:11,347 --> 00:35:12,347
Nephew.

844
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:15,520
The ancients said
we should indulge in spring sleep,

845
00:35:15,906 --> 00:35:18,063
but here I am, picking tea leaves
early in the morning,

846
00:35:18,146 --> 00:35:19,666
I can't even open my eyes.

847
00:35:22,840 --> 00:35:23,919
She has been

848
00:35:24,666 --> 00:35:26,866
finding more ways
to use your words against you.

849
00:35:29,223 --> 00:35:30,103
In that case,

850
00:35:30,186 --> 00:35:31,795
it seems like I do need to read more.

851
00:35:32,386 --> 00:35:34,303
If I had known this poem earlier,

852
00:35:34,386 --> 00:35:35,821
I wouldn't have to wake up early.

853
00:35:36,107 --> 00:35:37,666
That's right.

854
00:35:38,146 --> 00:35:39,587
You should read more.

855
00:35:40,000 --> 00:35:41,000
You see,

856
00:35:41,146 --> 00:35:42,626
you can even quote classics

857
00:35:42,780 --> 00:35:44,219
when you are arguing.

858
00:35:49,192 --> 00:35:50,313
There is a flower here.

859
00:35:50,800 --> 00:35:51,800
Leave it.

860
00:35:54,520 --> 00:35:55,825
In the three months of spring,

861
00:35:56,906 --> 00:35:57,946
do not kill the living,

862
00:35:59,107 --> 00:36:00,107
What does that mean?

863
00:36:15,706 --> 00:36:16,706
Meng Meng,

864
00:36:17,820 --> 00:36:19,060
are you feeling cold?

865
00:36:20,747 --> 00:36:21,747
Here. Put this on.

866
00:36:27,747 --> 00:36:28,747
What are you doing?

867
00:36:30,987 --> 00:36:31,987
Zhen Zhen,

868
00:36:32,307 --> 00:36:33,426
what are you doing here?

869
00:36:34,666 --> 00:36:35,783
I feel really cold too.

870
00:36:35,866 --> 00:36:37,432
Do you have any more clothes for me?

871
00:36:37,666 --> 00:36:38,543
No.

872
00:36:38,626 --> 00:36:39,823
Just hold yourself tight.

873
00:36:39,906 --> 00:36:40,823
You will be fine.

874
00:36:40,906 --> 00:36:42,664
No.

875
00:36:42,747 --> 00:36:45,667
Tou Tou, the way you talk is a bit...

876
00:36:45,805 --> 00:36:48,303
Come on, Li Quan,

877
00:36:48,386 --> 00:36:50,427
the wind is so strong.

878
00:36:50,560 --> 00:36:53,040
So strong. I'm weak.

879
00:36:53,320 --> 00:36:54,157
When the wind blows,

880
00:36:54,240 --> 00:36:55,543
I feel so sad.

881
00:36:55,626 --> 00:36:57,466
You just don't understand me.

882
00:37:01,186 --> 00:37:02,583
What's wrong with you guys?

883
00:37:02,666 --> 00:37:04,146
What is the meaning of this?

884
00:37:05,307 --> 00:37:06,583
I'm also girl.

885
00:37:06,666 --> 00:37:08,587
What's wrong with me feeling cold?

886
00:37:14,680 --> 00:37:15,680
This is annoying!

887
00:37:20,120 --> 00:37:21,294
Meng Meng, let me help you.

888
00:37:22,960 --> 00:37:23,960
Let's go.

889
00:37:26,960 --> 00:37:27,960
Come on.

890
00:37:32,480 --> 00:37:33,480
I'm leaving then.

891
00:37:39,827 --> 00:37:41,146
You're so disgusting.

892
00:37:49,666 --> 00:37:50,666
Ren Tian Zhen,

893
00:37:51,146 --> 00:37:52,225
have you lost your mind?

894
00:37:53,706 --> 00:37:56,224
Why are you so double-standard?

895
00:37:56,307 --> 00:37:59,107
You help everyone with
their baskets, except for me!

896
00:37:59,466 --> 00:38:00,466
You can't catch me.

897
00:38:03,067 --> 00:38:04,103
-Keep running.
-What are you doing?

898
00:38:04,186 --> 00:38:05,627
-Keep running.
-You...

899
00:38:06,426 --> 00:38:07,426
Wait.

900
00:38:12,119 --> 00:38:13,119
Ling Ian!

901
00:38:14,706 --> 00:38:16,386
Ling Ian, thank goodness I caught you.

902
00:38:16,520 --> 00:38:18,390
Otherwise, you would've fallen
into the pot,

903
00:38:18,747 --> 00:38:19,747
right?

904
00:38:21,307 --> 00:38:22,386
Let go, let go.

905
00:38:23,906 --> 00:38:24,906
Tou Tou.

906
00:38:26,107 --> 00:38:27,706
Don't be impulsive.

907
00:38:27,987 --> 00:38:29,904
No, Master, look at him.

908
00:38:29,987 --> 00:38:31,143
He carried the basket

909
00:38:31,226 --> 00:38:32,424
for every girl,

910
00:38:32,507 --> 00:38:33,383
but he wouldn't carry mine.

911
00:38:33,466 --> 00:38:34,704
-Why did he do that?
-You haven't paid back

912
00:38:34,787 --> 00:38:36,259
for Meng Meng's dad's glasses.

913
00:38:40,839 --> 00:38:41,839
Behave yourself.

914
00:38:48,587 --> 00:38:50,067
Come here. Fry the tea leaves.

915
00:38:50,747 --> 00:38:51,747
Coming.

916
00:38:52,192 --> 00:38:53,192
Leave this task

917
00:38:53,906 --> 00:38:55,386
to a chef.

918
00:38:55,706 --> 00:38:56,664
Are you okay, Mum?

919
00:38:56,747 --> 00:38:57,747
I'm fine.

920
00:38:58,547 --> 00:38:59,547
Dad is impressive.

921
00:39:01,426 --> 00:39:02,426
Very impressive.

922
00:39:06,992 --> 00:39:07,992
Go get another pot.

923
00:39:08,386 --> 00:39:09,386
Okay.

924
00:39:28,706 --> 00:39:29,706
Tou Tou.

925
00:39:29,906 --> 00:39:31,906
Tou Tou, come here.

926
00:39:32,386 --> 00:39:33,386
Come look at this.

927
00:39:36,587 --> 00:39:37,587
Hurry.

928
00:39:37,827 --> 00:39:38,827
Look at that.

929
00:39:43,547 --> 00:39:44,355
It's the Milky Way.

930
00:39:44,438 --> 00:39:45,840
-Isn't it beautiful?
-Yes.

931
00:39:53,827 --> 00:39:55,426
I heard it.

932
00:39:58,480 --> 00:39:59,641
You can even sing

933
00:40:00,005 --> 00:40:02,285
in different vocal parts?

934
00:40:03,587 --> 00:40:06,067
How do you sing so beautifully?

935
00:40:07,800 --> 00:40:08,881
Who's singing?

936
00:40:10,073 --> 00:40:11,063
Who's singing?

937
00:40:11,146 --> 00:40:13,186
Everything is singing.

938
00:40:14,386 --> 00:40:16,107
They have spirituality.

939
00:40:16,987 --> 00:40:19,307
The way you talk to them,

940
00:40:20,107 --> 00:40:22,386
and your attitude towards them,

941
00:40:23,146 --> 00:40:24,186
they know it.

942
00:40:27,579 --> 00:40:28,579
Tou Tou,

943
00:40:28,906 --> 00:40:30,426
can you locate the Big Dipper?

944
00:40:31,466 --> 00:40:33,587
Don't be silly, my dear nephew.

945
00:40:34,067 --> 00:40:35,224
If I could find the Big Dipper,

946
00:40:35,307 --> 00:40:37,143
would I have gotten lost
on the mountain that time?

947
00:40:37,226 --> 00:40:38,543
Would I not have found my way back?

948
00:40:38,626 --> 00:40:40,266
I will show you. Watch.

949
00:40:40,653 --> 00:40:41,740
The brightest ones there.

950
00:40:42,226 --> 00:40:47,226
One, two, three, four, five, six, seven.

951
00:40:48,706 --> 00:40:50,264
Picture it in your mind.

952
00:40:50,347 --> 00:40:52,866
Imagine the Big Dipper

953
00:40:53,547 --> 00:40:55,107
as a clock.

954
00:40:56,666 --> 00:40:59,863
When the Big Dipper points to Chen,

955
00:40:59,946 --> 00:41:01,164
it's the time of Grain Rain.

956
00:41:02,626 --> 00:41:04,186
-Chen?
-That's right.

957
00:41:04,987 --> 00:41:05,987
What time is that?

958
00:41:06,626 --> 00:41:07,987
From 7am to 9am,

959
00:41:08,587 --> 00:41:09,866
when you have breakfast.

960
00:41:10,987 --> 00:41:12,543
But why is it called Grain Rain?

961
00:41:12,626 --> 00:41:13,626
It's not raining here.

962
00:41:14,386 --> 00:41:16,426
It will rain at night.

963
00:41:17,107 --> 00:41:19,347
Grain Rain brings rain,

964
00:41:19,906 --> 00:41:21,107
indicating a good harvest.

